# Local Development Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your actual values
# .dev.vars is excluded from git and contains secrets for local development only

# Sentry Error Tracking (Optional)
# NOTE: Astro requires PUBLIC_ prefix for browser-accessible variables
#       Variables without PUBLIC_ prefix are server-only and NOT sent to the browser
#       SENTRY_DSN is technically "public" (embedded in browser JS) so it uses PUBLIC_
#       SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN is server-only (used for uploading source maps)
# Get your DSN from: https://sentry.io/settings/projects/
# Format: https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0
PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-public-key@o0.ingest.sentry.io/your-project-id
PUBLIC_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development
PUBLIC_SENTRY_RELEASE=local-dev

# Server-side Sentry configuration (NOT exposed to browser)
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=your-sentry-auth-token-for-source-map-uploads

# Cloudflare Bindings
# These are referenced in wrangler.jsonc and accessible via Astro.locals.runtime.env

# Example: D1 Database (if configured in wrangler.jsonc)
# DATABASE_URL=file:./local.db

# Example: R2 Object Storage (if configured)
# R2_BUCKET_NAME=my-local-bucket
# R2_BUCKET_ENDPOINT=https://bucket.r2.example.com

# Example: KV Namespace (if configured)
# SESSION_KV_NAMESPACE_ID=your-kv-namespace-id

# Custom Environment Variables
# Add any other environment variables your app needs here
# Example: API_KEY=your-api-key

# GitHub Production Deployment Setup
# For production, create GitHub Repository Variables (not secrets):
#
# VARIABLES (public - visible in browser):
# 1. PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN = your DSN from Sentry dashboard
# 2. PUBLIC_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT = production (or staging)
#
# SECRETS (encrypted - used by CI/CD only):
# 1. SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN (for automatic source map uploads)
# 2. CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN (for Pages deployment)
# 3. CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID (for Pages deployment)
